      action: "Inhibits dihydrofolate reductase (DHFR), blocking conversion of dihydrofolate to tetrahydrofolate required for thymidylate and purine synthesis; arrests DNA replication in rapidly dividing trophoblast cells, causing ectopic tissue involution without surgery; administered as single-dose (50 mg/m² IM) or two-dose protocol",
      sideEffects: "Nausea, vomiting, stomatitis, separation pain (abdominal cramping 2-7 days post-injection as ectopic tissue resolves), transient hCG rise days 1-4, bone marrow suppression, hepatotoxicity, photosensitivity, alopecia (rare at single-dose levels)",
      contra: "Hemodynamic instability, ruptured ectopic, fetal cardiac activity, immunodeficiency, hepatic disease (AST >2x normal), renal insufficiency (creatinine >1.5), blood dyscrasias (WBC <3000, platelets <100,000), breastfeeding, active pulmonary disease, peptic ulcer disease, hypersensitivity",
      pearl: "Success rates: single-dose 87-93% for hCG <5,000; drops to 68% for hCG >5,000; two-dose protocol improves success to 93% overall; patients MUST stop folic acid/prenatal vitamins before treatment; transient hCG rise days 1-4 is EXPECTED -- treatment response is assessed by ≥15% decline between days 4 and 7; separation pain must be differentiated from rupture (hemodynamically stable, no free fluid progression)"
